pulls.title: No xhr
pulls.body:
Changes include: 
- Minimized dependencies, so d3.js v3.5 is the only requirement.  Bootstrap, jquery and jquery-multiselect have been removed. This resulted led to several UI changes including:
  - unicode icons instead of glyphicons
  - click the "category" text instead of an icon to see the details page. 
  - removed the settings drop down with the "expand all" and "hide details" column
  - minor changes to search box appearance
  - standard multi-select fields for filters instead of bootstrap multiselect. 
  - standard table formatting (instead of bootstrap) on details table. 
- table.js now expects a json object using the standard [d3.csv()](https://github.com/d3/d3-3.x-api-reference/blob/master/CSV.md) formatting, instead of a path to a .csv. _This change breaks backwards compatibility with version 1.X_
- Added package.json and published to npm. 
- Simplified settings object. Removed settings.filterSettings, settings.defaults.prefterms and settings.defaults.diffcol are no longer used. The variables and settings objects will be fully merged in the next major release.
- Linked to [example gist]() in the wiki

releases.name: v3.1.0
releases.body:
Version 3.1.0 of the Adverse Event Explorer adds the following performance improvements:
- Refactored in-browser CSV generation that allows users to download the data directly from the chart
- Filtering the data impacts the data included in the CSV download
- CSVs will download with the named value attributes
- There are new settings to allow default filter values on initial load
- There are new settings to allow default display type

A full list of resolved issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/issues?q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3A3.1.0+is%3Aclosed).

releases.name: v3.0.0
releases.body:
Version 3.0.0 of the Adverse Event Explorer represents a major refactor, and includes many bug fixes and performance improvements. 
- Allow for filters on participant characteristics (like age and gender) as well as adverse event characteristics (like severity and relatedness to treatment).
- Consolidated all chart configuration in to a single settings object. This breaks backwards compatibility.
- Restructured code using modular build. 
- Refactored and simplified data flow, allowing for filters on detail tables.
- Made chart appearance options accessible via settings. 

A full list of resolved issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/milestone/2?closed=1).

releases.name: v2.0.0
releases.body:
This release of the AE Explorer simplifies the dependencies, adds npm support and introduces minor changes in the appearance and configuration of the charts. 

Changes include: 
- Minimized dependencies, so d3.js v3.5 is the only requirement.  Bootstrap, jquery and jquery-multiselect have been removed. This resulted led to several UI changes including:
  - unicode icons instead of glyphicons
  - click the "category" text instead of an icon to see the details page. 
  - removed the settings drop down with the "expand all" and "hide details" column
  - minor changes to search box appearance
  - standard multi-select fields for filters instead of bootstrap multiselect. 
  - standard table formatting (instead of bootstrap) on details table. 
- table.js now expects a json object using the standard [d3.csv()](https://github.com/d3/d3-3.x-api-reference/blob/master/CSV.md) formatting, instead of a path to a .csv. _This change breaks backwards compatibility with version 1.X_
- Added package.json and published to npm. 
- Simplified settings object. Removed settings.filterSettings, settings.defaults.prefterms and settings.defaults.diffcol are no longer used. The variables and settings objects will be fully merged in the next major release.
- Linked to [example gist](https://bl.ocks.org/jwildfire/b04788be10333e2dd55437807145fb51) in the wiki

issues.title: No Total column when group variable has only one level.
issues.body:
Per @nandriychuk, the issue arises when `groupCols = false`, `totalCol = true`, and `variables.group` has only one level.  The total column is not rendered, resulting in a table with only the _Category_ and _AE Rate by group_ columns.

Also, `variables.group` does not appear to be optional.

issues.title: Generalize the nesting to allow for n>2 levels.
Other graphical risk metrics
issues.body:
Proposal to be able to choose from ratios (Risk Ratio or the Odds Ratio) as risk metrics rather having the risk difference only for the AE dot plot.

If one would extend the data array with a time-to variable, one could also think about other values like hazard-ratios or even include on-demand Kaplan-Meier-Plots. However, this would require some more work....

Also, sometime you only want to compare to one single reference treatment (e.g. placebo) if you have multiple treatments. This would improve the readability of the graphical part as well.

Jack requested that we update the AE Explorer to include a way to interactively select subgrouping by age, gender, and site.  

Spencer said this shouldn't be too difficult since there is already a method that prepares the data given the grouping variable.  We will just need to ignore the groups argument that controls which groups are displayed.  Perhaps we could have a more complex groups argument that optionally accepts an array of group values.

issues.title: Styling differences with Bootstrap turned on in CAT
issues.body:
While testing https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/pull/93 we found the following styling differences.

With Bootstrap on:

- Font style is slightly different
- Search box is in the far right corner instead of closer to the middle
- Category names are blue instead of black
- When you search the number of matches is in a green box with white text instead of just plain black text
- There is slightly less vertical spacing between boxes in the header section
- When you search on a term and clear the search, the category names that were highlighted as a search result are black text instead of blue
- The "Return to Summary View" button is larger and blue with white text instead of grey with black text
- There are horizontal lines between each subject record in the listing view

These are all minor and I confirmed that all of them except the vertical spacing and horizontal line ones are already in the latest version of the renderer in RhoMAP.  We should discuss whether or not the other differences are worth addressing.

issues.title: Participant filters only include categories for participants with AEs
issues.body:
[This line of code](https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/blob/master/src/chart/controls/filters/custom/init.js#L12) doesn't match the configuration spec since "Participant" should be "participant". This means that the categories for participant filters only include options from participants with AEs. The result is a fairly major bug where records are silently dropped for filter levels that are not included in the (buggy filter). 

Fix is to simply update the line of code to the correct capitalization.

issues.title: sas: CSV for validation not doubling up double quotes
issues.body:
When a minorCategory value has double quotes within it, the CSV should double those double quotes. 
For instance:
"Decrease in heart's ability to pump blood during the "active" phas of the heartbeat (systole)"
Should actually appear as:
"Decrease in heart's ability to pump blood during the ""active"" phas of the heartbeat (systole)"

issues.title: Accept array of value_col/label objects as well as array of strings from variables.details.
Update naming conventions for settings object
issues.body:
Update chart arguments to be consistent with naming conventions of other safety charts.  Keep support of previous argument names until next major release.  This includes the following changes:

id -> id_col
major -> major_col
minor -> minor_col
group -> group_col
placeholderFlag -> missingValues
totalCol -> showTotalCol
diffCol -> showDiffCol
prefTerms -> showPrefTerms

issues.title: `filter:null` gives unexpected results
issues.body:
**Current behaviour**: If a user specifies `filters:null` the default filters are rendered. 
**Expected behaviour**: If a user specifies `filters:null` no filters are rendered.  

Side notes: 
- `null` is probably a more resonable default for filters
- `filter:[]` doesn't render any filters (this is fine)

cc: @bzkrouse

issues.title: Filters not behaving when raw data is stored as numeric
issues.body:
Not a problem with creating json via d3.csv() since everything is coerced to character, but can cause problems in other scenarios. 

Fix is easy, just coerce the value to character [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/blob/master/src/chart/util/prepareData.js#L42) and [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/aeexplorer/blob/master/src/chart/util/prepareData.js#L58). This: `return filter_d.currentValues.indexOf(rowData[filter_d.value_col])>-1` becomes this:             `return filter_d.currentValues.indexOf(""+rowData[filter_d.value_col])>-1`
